<MarkdownLayout title="Delete Account — soulMates" description="How to delete your soulMates account and all associated data.">

<h2>How to delete your account</h2>

<p>You can delete your soulMates account and all associated data directly from the app. Follow these steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Open the <strong>soulMates</strong> app on your device.</li>
  <li>Go to the <strong>Music Profile</strong> tab (the brain icon in the bottom navigation).</li>
  <li>Scroll to the bottom of the page.</li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Delete Account</strong> (in red).</li>
  <li>Confirm by tapping <strong>Delete</strong> in the dialog.</li>
</ol>

<h2>What gets deleted</h2>

<p>When you delete your account, the following data is permanently removed:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Your account and login credentials</li>
  <li>Your display profile (name and avatar)</li>
  <li>All your matches and compatibility data</li>
  <li>All chat rooms and messages associated with your account</li>
  <li>Your swipe history and music preference data</li>
</ul>

<p>Local data stored on your device (cached tracks and preferences) is also cleared when you delete your account.</p>

<h2>This action is permanent</h2>

<p>Account deletion cannot be undone. If you wish to use soulMates again, you will need to create a new account.</p>

<h2>Need help?</h2>

<p>If you are unable to access the app or need assistance deleting your account, contact us at <a href="mailto:soulMates@mail.provable.dev">soulMates@mail.provable.dev</a> with the email address associated with your account.</p>

</MarkdownLayout>
